history.content: I'm sorry to say but I do not know exactly how swaps work - only that they are problematic, with unexpected outcomes & I usually recommend that people do not use the feature because they are impossible to cancel.  The only info I can offer is this link: https://sis.berkeley.edu/help/enrollment-faq/swap

There’s still currently 121 (+ 2 perhaps) open reserved seats for CS184 right now showing in the class schedule. Is this number accurate? I ask because I was somehow enrolled into it off the waitlist but I didn’t get dropped from the class I wanted to swap it with, so now I’m enrolled in 17 units which is strange. I’m wondering though if I was enrolled because there were still reserved seats open and if so, why hasn’t everyone in the waitlist who qualifies for those seats been enrolled as well? My friend who is also an EECS major and was only about 30 spots below me on the waitlist has only moved up like 10 spots while I went from around 29th in line to enrolled.
